Assuming you&#39;re doing this line-by-line (since there&#39;s no `g` on the regular expression), then as [Federico klez Culloca said](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/58499874/javascript-elegant-regular-expression#comment103328650_58499874), remove the `.` in `.*`. Also note that `&#39;$1 &#39; + 2017 + &#39; $2&#39;` is more directly written simply `&#39;$1 2017 $2&#39;`:

    name.replace(/([a-zA-Z\s]*)([-]?)/, &#39;$1 2017 $2&#39;)
    // No . here ------------^

Live Example:

